00:19:17.999 --> 00:19:21.166
The fact that bulgur is
chosen as a perfect food

00:19:36.999 --> 00:19:40.542
to nourish people during times

00:19:40.709 --> 00:19:42.458
when their nutrition
is highly compromised

00:19:42.625 --> 00:19:44.999
only attests to this
grain's already inherent

00:19:45.083 --> 00:19:48.125
exceptional
properties and value.

00:19:48.291 --> 00:19:50.999
Through fortification efforts,
it will not be surprising

00:19:51.583 --> 00:19:55.458
if bulgur surpasses
the superfood level

00:19:55.625 --> 00:19:59.250
and starts a totally new

00:19:59.417 --> 00:20:01.083
and more superior food category.

00:20:01.250 --> 00:20:03.875
Most bulgur today,
specially the kind

00:20:17.834 --> 00:20:20.208
that is exported
around the world,

00:20:20.375 --> 00:20:22.625
is processed using
modern facilities.

00:20:22.792 --> 00:20:26.166
But the ancient method lives on

00:20:26.333 --> 00:20:28.417
in some small villages
in Eastern Mediterranean.

00:20:28.583 --> 00:20:31.834
Since bulgur is already
partially cooked,

00:20:32.999 --> 00:20:35.999
it enjoys a longer shelf life

00:20:36.125 --> 00:20:38.458
and preparation is much simpler
compared to other grains.

00:20:38.625 --> 00:20:42.667
It's like instant cereal,

00:20:43.166 --> 00:20:44.999
because you can just
pour boiling water,

00:20:45.083 --> 00:20:47.709
soak it for 30 to 40 minutes,

00:20:47.875 --> 00:20:49.959
drain it, and then voilà.

00:20:49.999 --> 00:20:52.250
You now have a bulgur pilaf.

00:20:52.417 --> 00:20:55.041
Bulgur absorbs water, expands,

00:20:55.208 --> 00:20:58.000
and doubles, even
triples in volume

00:20:58.166 --> 00:21:00.999
so make sure you use big pots.

00:21:01.041 --> 00:21:03.999
Here are some recipe
ideas for you to try.

00:21:04.792 --> 00:21:07.917
Vegan bulgur pilaf
with mushrooms.

00:21:07.999 --> 00:21:10.583
For this recipe you will need

00:21:11.208 --> 00:21:13.083
one and one half cups
of uncooked bulgur,

00:21:13.250 --> 00:21:16.291
three cups of water,

00:21:16.458 --> 00:21:18.166
three tablespoons of
butter or vegan margarine,

00:21:18.333 --> 00:21:21.500
two cups sliced mushrooms,

00:21:21.667 --> 00:21:23.834
one bunch of chopped
green onions,

00:21:24.542 --> 00:21:27.333
one medium chopped
red bell pepper,

00:21:27.500 --> 00:21:30.250
two tablespoons of lime juice,

00:21:30.417 --> 00:21:32.959
three tablespoons
of dry white wine,

00:21:32.999 --> 00:21:35.667
one quarter cup of
chopped fresh parsley,

00:21:35.834 --> 00:21:38.458
one tablespoon of dried basil,

00:21:38.999 --> 00:21:41.625
and one teaspoon each
of salt and pepper.

00:21:41.792 --> 00:21:44.750
Start by cooking the
bulgur in a pot of water

00:21:45.166 --> 00:21:48.375
for five minutes.

00:21:48.542 --> 00:21:50.000
Remove the pot from the heat,

00:21:50.166 --> 00:21:51.999
but let it stand for
five more minutes

00:21:52.041 --> 00:21:54.583
so the bulgur can start
absorbing water, then drain.

00:21:54.750 --> 00:21:58.500
In a large skillet
over medium heat

00:21:58.999 --> 00:22:01.458
melt the butter and
sauté the mushrooms,

00:22:01.625 --> 00:22:04.000
onions, and peppers.

00:22:04.166 --> 00:22:06.041
Once the onions are translucent,

00:22:06.709 --> 00:22:08.542
remove the skillet
from the heat.

00:22:08.709 --> 00:22:10.959
Then add the lemon
juice, wine, parsley,

00:22:10.999 --> 00:22:14.083
basil, salt, and pepper.

00:22:14.250 --> 00:22:16.834
Mix with bulgur and serve.

00:22:16.999 --> 00:22:19.542
Another must-try recipe

00:22:20.750 --> 00:22:22.750
is sprouts and
bulgur sandwiches.

00:22:22.917 --> 00:22:25.417
Prepare the following.

00:22:25.583 --> 00:22:26.999
One half cup of fine bulgur,

00:22:27.041 --> 00:22:29.375
one cup of water,

00:22:29.999 --> 00:22:31.417
226.8g low fat yogurt,

00:22:31.999 --> 00:22:35.667
one quarter of a cup of
fat-free salad dressing,

00:22:36.291 --> 00:22:39.834
one and one half
teaspoons of curry powder,

00:22:39.999 --> 00:22:42.917
one cup of shredded carrots,

00:22:42.999 --> 00:22:45.166
one half cup of chopped apple,

00:22:45.333 --> 00:22:47.917
one third cup of
coarsely chopped peanuts,

00:22:47.999 --> 00:22:51.125
two cups of fresh bean sprouts,

00:22:51.291 --> 00:22:53.999
and eight very thin slices
of toasted wheat bread.

00:22:53.999 --> 00:22:57.917
First, thoroughly rinse
bulgur under cold water,

00:22:58.999 --> 00:23:02.999
then stir in the bulgur in a pot

00:23:02.999 --> 00:23:04.999
of one cup of boiling water.

00:23:05.125 --> 00:23:07.625
Remove from heat.

00:23:07.792 --> 00:23:09.000
Let it stand uncovered
for 20 minutes,

00:23:09.166 --> 00:23:11.917
before draining and
squeezing excess water.

00:23:11.999 --> 00:23:14.999
Second, in a bowl combine
yogurt, salad dressing,

00:23:15.667 --> 00:23:19.125
or mayonnaise and curry powder.

00:23:19.291 --> 00:23:21.959
Stir until everything
is evenly incorporated.

00:23:22.542 --> 00:23:25.709
Third, put the bulgur, carrots,

00:23:26.250 --> 00:23:28.999
apple and peanuts in
the yogurt mixture.

00:23:29.125 --> 00:23:32.458
Mix, cover, and then
refrigerate until serving time.

00:23:32.999 --> 00:23:37.375
To serve, divide and
arrange the sprouts

00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:41.208
on four wheat toasts.

00:23:41.375 --> 00:23:43.500
Scoop and spread bulgur mixture,

00:23:43.667 --> 00:23:45.999
and then top with the
rest of the wheat toasts.

00:23:45.999 --> 00:23:48.750
You can still enjoy bulgur using

00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:51.999
traditional tabbouleh recipes.

00:23:52.041 --> 00:23:54.709
But in today's evolving cuisines

00:23:54.875 --> 00:23:57.000
and growing anticipation
for new food ideas,

00:23:57.166 --> 00:24:00.583
utilizing bulgur in your
gastronomic adventures

00:24:00.750 --> 00:24:04.125
is truly a must.

